<p>A wide range of contributors and attendees with diverse backgrounds from across the world wiil be participating in the meeting. A small sampling of the speakers includes Amir Bitran, Harvard University, speaking on ‚ÄúTowards design of folding inhibitors against SARS-CoV-2 proteins‚Äù, Kevin Thompson, National Science Foundation, discussing ‚ÄúCC* and campus computing‚Äù, and James P. Howard, Johns Hopkins Applied Physics Laboratory, will be talking about ‚ÄúModeling demand for medical resources‚Äù. The full list of contributors can be found on <a href="https://indico.fnal.gov/event/47040/contributions/">the Contributors page</a>.</p>

<p>The daily meeting topics are:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Monday:</strong> State of OSG; David Swanson Award recipients; Impact on Research</li>
  <li><strong>Tuesday:</strong> Campus Services and Experiences; NSF Campus Cyberinfrastructure (CC*)</li>
  <li><strong>Wednesday:</strong> OSG Agility and Technology Advancements</li>
  <li><strong>Thursday:</strong> Impact on Multi-Institutional Collaborations</li>
  <li><strong>Friday:</strong> U.S. ATLAS and CMS Projects</li>
</ul>

